kube-scheduler- Decides which pod will be deployed where(i mean, in which node). This decision is based on the resource requirements of the pod and the availability of resources on a node.
Config file location: /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-scheduler.yaml

Etcd- Database(runs at port 2379)

kubelet- Deploys pods on nodes. Kubelet only runs on worker nodes.

kube-proxy- Runs on each node in k8s including control plane node. It enables services (like databases) to reach the database pod. It is deployed as daemonset.
